This is Perl module DBIx::QueryLog::Fluent.

INSTALLATION

Type the following command:

    $ curl -L http://cpanmin.us | perl - DBIx::QueryLog::Fluent

Or install cpanm and then run the following command to install
DBIx::QueryLog::Fluent:

    $ cpanm DBIx::QueryLog::Fluent

If you get an archive of this distribution, unpack it and build it
as per the usual:

    $ tar xzf DBIx-QueryLog-Fluent-$version.tar.gz
    $ cd DBIx-QueryLog-Fluent-$version
    $ perl Makefile.PL
    $ make && make test

Then install it:

    $ make install

DOCUMENTATION

DBIx::QueryLog::Fluent documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    $ perldoc DBIx::QueryLog::Fluent

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

